                <h1>Maya Angelou: Fascinating Facts About a Literary Legend</h1>
                <p>Maya Angelou, celebrated poet and civil rights activist, was born in 1928 in St. Louis. She overcame a difficult childhood, including trauma and racism, which profoundly influenced her work. Angelou's most famous work, "I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings," details her life experiences. She received numerous accolades, including the Presidential Medal of Freedom.</p>
